Sources include The New York Times Sunday travel section and leading travel writers . ) & HT ; ( PLEASE NOTE : This article has been transmitted twice _ into the `` t '' travel news and `` l '' lifestyle news files . ) & HT ; By MARVINE HOWE ( Distributed by New York Times Special Features ) & HT ; In honor of that intrepid seafarer Vasco da Gama and his journey to India 500 years ago , the Portuguese have organized celebrations the likes of which have never been seen in this onetime imperial capital .
& HT ; On May 22 , Lisbon opened the gates to Expo ' 98 , with a record participation of 154 countries and the theme `` The Oceans , a Heritage for the Future . ''
& HT ; During Expo 's four-month run , visitors can discover the beauty , riches and challenges of the seas through scores of exhibits .
There will also be nautical competitions , daily multimedia shows , live entertainment and food from around the world .
& HT ; The industrial wasteland on Lisbon 's east side is being replaced with new residences and businesses and , of course , Expo , a 150-acre fairgrounds with international exhibits , a riverside esplanade , exotic gardens and a panoramic cable car along three miles of riverfront .
& HT ; To avoid a post-Expo ghost town , the main pavilions will be turned into cultural sites , like an aquarium , a science museum and a theater .
& HT ; Expo has parking for 17,000 vehicles , but the public is urged to use bus , subway , train or taxi to the new Oriente Station , which rises like a forest of steel and glass near Expo 's eastern gate .
There will also be regular ferries from the Cais do Sodre river terminal .
& HT ; Also on the eastern periphery , the new 10-mile-long Vasco da Gama Bridge over the Tagus River estuary connects with highways to the Algarve and Spain .
& HT ; On the northern ring is Colombo , one of Europe 's largest shopping centers , honoring another great explorer .
This popular new destination includes 425 shops , 10 movie theaters and an amusement park .
& HT ; All around the city , ancient monuments and neighborhoods have been refurbished and new green spaces planted .
But the new highways and Metro stations are a maze of works in progress , causing dust and delays .
EVENTS & HT ; Each day of Expo ' 98 , which runs until Sept. 30 , its showpiece event , a multimedia program called `` Ocean Myths and Legends , '' will be presented at the giant UFO-like Utopia Pavilion at noon , 3 , 5 and 9 p.m. & HT ; People in carnivalesque sea-monster costumes will provide street shows all day long , and incredible-looking water-themed machines will parade around at sunset .
& HT ; Artistic and folk groups will perform at the Dock Amphitheater and other open areas in the late afternoon .
& HT ; Small ensembles offer fado ( Portuguese soul music ) , jazz , classical music , hip-hop and rock at a dozen open-air stages starting at about 8 : 30 p.m. Evenings close with Midnight Tea , an open-air disco from midnight to 2 a.m. & HT ; The fairgrounds themselves are open from 9 a.m. to 3 a.m. daily .
& HT ; International performers are scheduled every evening .
The Greek Art Theater will perform `` The Birds '' by Aristophanes on June 11 at 9 : 30 p.m. at the Dock amphitheater .
Free tickets are available at the national pavilions .
& HT ; On July 25 some 120 tall ships in the Cutty Sark Tall Ships ' Race start to arrive in Lisbon for the Vasco da Gama Memorial International Regatta July 31 to Aug. 3.
& HT ; A ticket for Expo ' 98 good for one day and night is $ 28 ; a one-night ticket good after 8 p.m. is $ 11 .
The three-day pass is $ 70 and three-month pass $ 285 .
Children 5 to 14 and people over 64 pay half price .
Telephone ( 351 - 1 ) 868 - 0426 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 868 - 1800 .
& HT ; Many cultural events will coincide with Expo .
Les Ballets C. de la B. from Belgium will perform `` They Feed , we / Eat , Eat , Eat , '' choreographed by Van den Broeck on June 19 and 20 and the premiere of the dance-drama `` Bach , '' set to music by Bach , on July 1 , 2 and 3 , both at 10 p.m. at the Belem Cultural Center 's Grand Auditorium , Praca do Imperio at Belem .
Tickets are $ 5.80 to $ 17 ; ( 351 - 1 ) 361 - 2400 .
& HT ; The Royal Concertgebouw of Amsterdam , conducted by Sir Colin Davis , will perform the Overture to Berlioz 's `` Benvenuto Cellini , '' with the pianist Maria Joao Pires playing Chopin 's Concerto No. 1 , on June 25 , and Berlioz 's `` Damnation of Faust '' on June 26 .
& HT ; Both programs begin at 9 : 30 p.m. at the Coliseu dos Recreios , Rua Portas de Santo Antao .
Tickets : $ 28 to $ 85 ; ( 351 - 1 ) 796 - 6306 .
& HT ; Bizet 's `` Carmen , '' directed by Giuseppe Raffa and starring Dulce Pontes in the title role , will be performed July 1 to 15 , nightly except Thursdays at 10 at the Campo Pequeno Bullring , Praca de Touros .
Tickets are $ 20 to $ 170 ; ( 351 - 1 ) 303 - 3113 .
SIGHTSEEING & HT ; The main attraction at Expo is the Oceanarium , one of Europe 's largest aquariums , designed by the American architect Peter Chermayeff .
& HT ; Visitors are surrounded by re-creations of environments of the Atlantic , Pacific , Indian and Antarctic Oceans , culminating in a Global Ocean .
& HT ; The Portuguese pavilion , overlooking Olivais Dock , will recount the country 's long struggle to master the seas .
Other pavilions will provide interactive experiences .
& HT ; Germany will offer a virtual journey to Oceanis , an underwater station equipped with the latest marine research technology .
& HT ; The United States pavilion is a showcase for American technology in diving , charting the ocean bottom and protecting the deep-sea environment .
& HT ; By the river , a huge abstract wave of stainless steel will be inscribed with the names of Portuguese-American contributors to the project .
& HT ; Expo has provided the inspiration for renovation projects in neighborhoods and landmarks throughout the city .
& HT ; Sao Jorge Castle , atop Lisbon 's highest hill and dating from Roman times , has been restored , and now includes a giant periscope ( see all of Lisbon for $ 1.70 ) and tourism information office .
& HT ; The castle , opening onto Rua Chao da Feira , is an oasis of shady terraces , towers and ramparts around the old palace , used for official receptions , a luxury restaurant in the walls and , soon to open , an esplanade cafe .
Open daily in summer 9 a.m. to 8 p.m. & HT ; The surrounding medieval neighborhood of Castelo , a jumble of tiny houses with iron balconies and patios but few modern conveniences , is being rehabilitated .
& HT ; And down the hill , the Moorish quarter of Alfama _ with its orange-tile roofs , cobblestone alleys and flowering balconies _ has also been spruced up .
& HT ; Near the 12th - century Se , or cathedral , the old customhouse has undergone major work and will open in mid-June as the Fado Museum , dedicated to the singers and their way of life .
No telephone yet .
& HT ; The Baixa , or downtown area , a lovely ensemble of 18th - century offices , banks and shops , is also getting a face lift .
& HT ; Praca do Comercio , a handsome square of bright yellow government buildings facing the river , is no longer spoiled by a parking lot .
& HT ; Historic buildings like Dona Maria II Theater and the 18th - century Cafe Nicola have been restored .
& HT ; Reconstruction is almost finished in the Chiado , the city 's most fashionable shopping neighborhood before it was devastated by fire in 1988 .
& HT ; The new Chiado Museum for Contemporary Art stands on the site of a 17th - century monastery , 6 Rua Serpa Pinto , ( 351 - 1 ) 343 - 2148 .
& HT ; Belem , a western suburb , is Lisbon 's monument zone .
The 16th - century Jeronimos Monastery and Belem Tower have just undergone repairs .
& HT ; Nearby , the Monument to the Discoveries , built in 1960 , honors Prince Henry the Navigator .
& HT ; The vast fortresslike Belem Cultural Center , built in 1993 , offers music and dance programs and art exhibitions .
& HT ; A new grassy esplanade runs along the riverfront from Belem to Alcantara , where decrepit warehouses have been converted into cafes , restaurants and discos .
& HT ; The National Museum of Azulejos , 4 Rua Madre de Deus , ( 351 - 1 ) 814 - 7747 , has marvelous decorative tiles .
WHERE TO STAY & HT ; Reservations promise to be difficult during Expo , and prices higher than normal .
& HT ; Only one hotel is open on the Expo site : the Oriente , ( 351 - 1 ) 893 - 0000 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 893 - 0099 , a bright new apartment-hotel with 116 rooms with kitchenettes and simple decor .
A double is $ 160 .
& HT ; Centrally situated , Hotel Eduardo VII , 5 Avenida Fontes Pereira Melo ( 351 - 1 ) 353 - 0141 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 353 - 3879 , has been remodeled .
It has 130 rooms with park and river views .
A double is $ 125 with breakfast .
& HT ; Budget : Away from downtown , near Lisbon University , the renovated Hotel Lisboa Penta , Avenida Combatentes ( 351 - 1 ) 726 - 4054 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 726 - 4418 , has 600 comfortable rooms with views of central Lisbon and Monsanto Park .
A double is $ 90 , with breakfast .
& HT ; Hotel Amazonia , also outside the center at 12 - 20 Travessa Fabrica dos Pentes ; ( 351 - 1 ) 387 - 7006 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 387 - 9090 , in the quiet Amoreiras section near the 18th - century aqueduct , has 192 comfortable modern rooms .
A double is $ 100 with breakfast .
& HT ; Luxury : Overlooking Eduardo VII Park , the Ritz , 88 Rua Rodrigo da Fonseca ; ( 351 - 1 ) 383 - 2020 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 383 - 1783 , became a Four Seasons Hotel this year , and has been renovated with new beige carpets and gray and yellow marble in the hall .
& HT ; The 280 rooms still feature oversize marble bathrooms and private balconies .
A double is $ 335 .
& HT ; Formerly a private mansion , Hotel da Lapa , 4 Rua do Pau da Bandeira ; ( 351 - 1 ) 395 - 0005 , fax ( 351 - 1 ) 395 - 0665 , is on a hill in the elegant diplomatic quarter .
It has a richly decorated lobby and banquet hall , and the 94 spacious rooms are tastefully done .
& HT ; The large balconies overlook lush gardens with a fountain and pool .
A double is $ 270 .
WHERE TO EAT & HT ; About 80 restaurants and kiosks inside Expo will offer a range of cuisines and prices .
& HT ; At a Turkish restaurant run by Istanbul 's Divan Hotel , specialties include sea bass in parchment ( dinner for two with wine is about $ 50 ) , and Portugal 's Panoramic Tower has spectacular views to accompany local favorites like cataplana ( steamed pork and clams ) for $ 68 to $ 114 for two .
& HT ; In the Chiado , Cervejaria da Trindade , 20 C Rua da Trindade , ( 351 - 1 ) 342 - 3506 , a popular beer hall in a former monastery , specializes in beefsteak but also serves tasty grilled sole and other fish .
Dinner for two with beer or wine , about $ 22 .
& HT ; For Old World gilt , mirrors , crystal chandeliers and attentive service , the place is Tavares , 37 Rua da Misericordia , ( 351 - 1 ) 342 - 1112 .
Closed Sunday afternoon and Saturday .
Specialties include stuffed crab and duck with prunes .
Dinner for two with wine , $ 75 .
& HT ; Popular with the diplomatic community , Ja Sei ! , 202 Avenida Brasilia in Belem , ( 351 - 1 ) 301 - 5969 , serves high-quality Portuguese fare like roast lamb with thyme sauce , with a terrific view of the Tagus .
Dinner for two with wine , $ 60 .
Closed Saturdays and Sunday evening .
